   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Give prevention tool to 10,000 indigenous children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We created this proyect because we need to translate to 3 indigenous languages: mixteco, zapoteco and amuzgo, the&quot;Filipons T-Shirt&quot; tale. Filipon helps children to be aware of the importance of learning how to take care of their bodies and to seek for help when they need it. Throughout the story, they will understand that there are some people&apos;s actions that &quot;stain&quot; the brightness of their hearts and hurts their &quot;self-esteem,&quot; but it also teaches them how to identify their protective adult.</narrative>
  </description>
